user statistics

row.info <- data.frame(name = row.names(rating.mat2), count = rowCounts(rating.mat), meanRate = rowMeans(rating.mat))
row.info$name <- factor(row.info$name, levels = row.info[order(row.info$count, decreasing = T), 'name'])

ggplot(row.info, aes(x = name, y=count, fill= count))+   theme_bw()+
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity')+theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=-90, hjust=0.2, vjust = 0.2))+
  scale_y_continuous('num of ratings', breaks = seq(0,100,10)) + xlab('user')

ggplot(row.info, aes(x = name, y=meanRate, fill= meanRate))+   theme_bw()+
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity')+theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=-90, hjust=0.2, vjust = 0.2))+
  scale_y_continuous('avg ratings', breaks = seq(0,5,1)) + xlab('user')

ggplot(row.info, aes(x = name, y=count, fill= count))+   theme_bw()+
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity')+theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=-90, hjust=0.2, vjust = 0.2))+
  geom_line(aes(y= meanRate*20, group = 1), col = 'red')+
  scale_y_continuous('num of ratings', breaks = seq(0,100,10), sec.axis=sec_axis(~./20, name="avg ratings")) + 
  xlab('user')

recommender

USER-BASED Collarborative Filtering

rmodel <- Recommender(rating.mat, method = 'UBCF')
my_id <- 'guest1'
rowidx <- which(row.names(rating.mat2) == my_id)

recom <- predict(rmodel, rating.mat[rowidx], n = 10)
recom_list <- as(recom, 'list')[[1]]
idx <- sapply(recom_list, FUN = function(x) {which(movie.info.reduced$movie_ID == x)})
movie.info.reduced[idx, ]
